metadata.name: Rough Cuts #378
metadata.description:
Abstract generative artwork that explores composition and form by cutting canvas with straight lines. Coded brushwork gives a real-painting look to each piece.

Options:

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, July, 2022.

metadata.name: Girandola #219
metadata.description:
Girandola is a project that strives to show the strength of programming to create very full and complex art using simple shapes, colors and iteration.

The concept of drawing shapes around an expanding radius, en masse, with different colors, rotations, outlines and opacities is all we have here. Highly variable, with outputs ranging from thousands to close to 1 million shapes can produce a vast array of imagery that would be impossible without the power of iteration that only digital art can provide.

Controls
--------
[mouse click] - start/stop the sketch
[r] - redraw the sketch
[s] - save a .png

URL Params
----------
?size=xxxx where xxxx is a size in pixels you'd like to render

metadata.name: Zusammen #106
metadata.description:
The flow of colors across an infinitely maleable grid. Zusammen is built using a framebuffer setup in p5js sampling a rendered direction field to determine the pixel "push" direction, speed, and offsets.

You can run this in fullscreen as instructed below. Doing so will render at the browser's width and height, which will look quite different from the preview version, but will still use the same colors and rules as your token. This can be useful for making wallpapers etc.

You can also continue to run the simulation after it has stopped by hitting the spacebar. This will allow you to further explore the infinite generative space of the piece.

Made with p5js.

Double click to download
Add &highres=true to the URL to get a higher resolution output
Add &fullscreen=true to render to the browser size. N.B. outputs will be somewhat different than the regular view

license information in license.md
